WEBVTT

00:08.141 --> 00:09.174
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

00:09.176 --> 00:10.776
♪ La la la ♪

00:10.778 --> 00:12.310
♪ La la la la la la ♪

00:12.312 --> 00:13.245
♪ La la la ♪

00:13.247 --> 00:14.847
♪ La la la la la la ♪

00:14.849 --> 00:18.183
♪ La la la-a la-a la ♪

00:18.185 --> 00:19.418
[Rumbling, creature growling]

00:19.420 --> 00:20.786
Holy sh--

00:20.788 --> 00:22.387
[Creature growling]

00:22.389 --> 00:25.624
[All screaming]

00:25.626 --> 00:34.599
♪♪

00:34.601 --> 00:43.542
♪♪

00:43.544 --> 00:46.078
Aaaah! Aah!

00:46.080 --> 00:47.880
[Growling]

00:47.882 --> 00:51.216
All right, Lenny.
Move it along.

00:51.218 --> 00:52.484
What's the charge?

00:52.486 --> 00:54.219
Disturbing the peace.

00:54.221 --> 00:58.023
Peace? You call this peace?!
It's hypnosis!

00:58.025 --> 01:00.492
These people aren't alive!

01:00.494 --> 01:03.295
They've been bought off
with toaster ovens

01:03.297 --> 01:05.164
and push-button phones!

01:05.166 --> 01:07.065
Go home to your wife,
Lenny.

01:09.170 --> 01:10.969
All right.
Can you help me down?

01:10.971 --> 01:12.704
I-I tweaked my back
the other day.

01:12.706 --> 01:13.972
-Oh, no.
-Aah!

01:13.974 --> 01:15.774
-You okay?
-Yeah, I'm okay.

01:15.776 --> 01:16.708
Thank --
You're very sweet.

01:16.710 --> 01:18.110
-Oh. Thank you.
-Thank you.

01:18.112 --> 01:19.511
Thank you. Very sweet.

01:19.513 --> 01:21.847
Thanks a lot.
Thanks a lot.

01:21.849 --> 01:23.882
-[Growls]
-Ha-ha-ha...ha.

01:23.884 --> 01:27.586
I'm gonna go get
some soup. [Growls]

01:27.588 --> 01:30.122
All right. I'll bite.

01:31.458 --> 01:35.594
Oh, that is
Leonard Walinsky,

01:35.596 --> 01:37.863
the town gorilla.

01:37.865 --> 01:39.865
Say what, now?
Leonard Walinsky

01:39.867 --> 01:41.933
was the number-one
birthday-party gorilla

01:41.935 --> 01:44.403
in New Hampshire --
booked out years in advance.

01:44.405 --> 01:46.071
So, what happened?

01:46.073 --> 01:48.139
One year, little
Sally O'Brien --

01:48.141 --> 01:50.075
nice girl,
but she didn't want

01:50.077 --> 01:53.211
a gorilla at<i> her</i>
birthday party.

01:53.213 --> 01:54.813
She wanted a princess.

01:54.815 --> 01:56.348
Everyone thought
she was crazy,

01:56.350 --> 01:58.884
but she went ahead
with it.

01:58.886 --> 02:04.290
The party was a smash, and then
everybody wanted a princess.

02:04.292 --> 02:06.291
And that?

02:06.293 --> 02:09.027
That was the end
of Leonard Walinsky.

02:09.029 --> 02:10.161
It's a pretty sad story.

02:10.163 --> 02:11.963
I'm surprised you haven't
heard it by now.

02:11.965 --> 02:13.932
I don't know. I bet
every town's got a gorilla,

02:13.934 --> 02:17.102
and every gorilla
has the same story.

02:17.104 --> 02:20.772
Tucker Fong's
Curiosity Pagoda?

02:20.774 --> 02:22.241
What happened
to the erotic bakery?

02:22.243 --> 02:23.909
Caligula's Fist?

02:23.911 --> 02:25.444
Ooh, they closed.

02:25.446 --> 02:28.647
Aww. I loved
their sticky buns.

02:28.649 --> 02:30.115
Let's check this out.

02:30.117 --> 02:32.651
[Door bell jingles]

02:32.653 --> 02:35.187
[Door closes, bell jingles]

02:35.189 --> 02:37.456
[Eerie music plays]

02:37.458 --> 02:43.362
♪♪

02:43.364 --> 02:49.134
♪♪

02:49.136 --> 02:51.103
[Sniffs]

02:51.105 --> 02:53.405
Oh, man.

02:53.407 --> 02:55.207
This is so cool.

02:55.209 --> 02:57.609
I should get this for Grace.

02:57.611 --> 02:59.378
[Shouts]

03:02.016 --> 03:04.550
You -- You must be Tucker.

03:05.719 --> 03:08.687
Uh, how -- h-how much
is, uh, is that?

03:08.689 --> 03:10.121
Is gift?

03:10.123 --> 03:12.490
For my daughter.
H-Her birthday is Sunday.

03:12.492 --> 03:14.026
No, no.

03:14.028 --> 03:16.028
This not for
your daughter.

03:16.030 --> 03:17.896
This for your<i> friend.</i>

03:17.898 --> 03:20.099
Uh, f-for my...friend?

03:20.101 --> 03:22.902
Angry man.
Always yelling.

03:22.904 --> 03:24.970
Oh!
How do you know Stan?

03:24.972 --> 03:27.840
Stan! Yes, Stan!
Stan Miller!

03:27.842 --> 03:29.975
-Yeah.
-This for him.

03:29.977 --> 03:31.309
-[Giggles]
-Huh.

03:31.311 --> 03:32.378
[Radio crackles]

03:32.380 --> 03:35.981
I find something else
for your daughter.

03:35.983 --> 03:38.650
I come back.

03:38.652 --> 03:40.652
Yep, it's Lenny.

03:40.654 --> 03:42.721
He's in front
of the post office

03:42.723 --> 03:44.723
yelling about getting
the band back together.

03:44.725 --> 03:46.992
Well, nothing illegal
about that.

03:46.994 --> 03:50.195
He's also having sex
with a mailbox.

03:50.197 --> 03:51.530
Let's roll.

03:51.532 --> 03:52.932
Isn't this a job
for the feds?

03:52.934 --> 03:55.667
[Ominous music plays]

03:55.669 --> 03:56.868
♪♪

03:56.870 --> 03:59.671
[Door closes, bell jingles]

03:59.673 --> 04:02.474
♪♪

04:02.476 --> 04:09.147
♪♪

04:09.149 --> 04:15.821
♪♪

04:15.823 --> 04:22.294
♪♪

04:22.296 --> 04:24.029
So, let me
get this straight.

04:24.031 --> 04:26.632
In your America,
a fake gorilla

04:26.634 --> 04:28.633
and a mailbox
can't get together.

04:28.635 --> 04:30.502
Good to know!
Good to know!

04:30.504 --> 04:32.637
Man:
Sheriff! Help!

04:32.639 --> 04:34.272
-Ohh!
-Help!

04:34.274 --> 04:35.707
No, no, no, no.

04:35.709 --> 04:38.176
-Help!
-What are you doing here?

04:38.178 --> 04:39.945
Our daughter's birthday's
on Sunday.

04:39.947 --> 04:41.780
Yeah, that's why
you're taking her

04:41.782 --> 04:43.915
to see her grandparents
next weekend.

04:43.917 --> 04:45.784
Right, which now I can't.

04:45.786 --> 04:48.119
-Great.
-Don't. Don't.

04:48.121 --> 04:50.022
-Listen.
-Mm-hmm?

04:50.024 --> 04:51.990
[Whispering]
I'm in love.

04:51.992 --> 04:54.859
Ohh.
Congratulations!

04:54.861 --> 04:56.928
-Thank you.
-Okay, well...

04:56.930 --> 04:59.397
No, I'm not --
There's not a hug happening.

04:59.399 --> 05:01.267
She's in this band
called The Indigo Girls,

05:01.269 --> 05:03.335
and I'm following them
around this summer.

05:03.337 --> 05:05.604
Wh-- Did you at least
get her a gift?

05:05.606 --> 05:07.940
-We technically haven't met.
-Your daughter!

05:07.942 --> 05:09.608
-Did I get her a gift?!
-Yeah!

05:09.610 --> 05:10.675
-W-- My God.
-You did?!

05:10.677 --> 05:12.511
-Yes. Now --
-What'd ya get her?

05:12.513 --> 05:15.947
Okay, imagine the look
on our daughter's face

05:15.949 --> 05:19.618
when I hand her the keys
to her very own...

05:19.620 --> 05:21.086
storage unit.

05:21.088 --> 05:22.620
It's in Maine.

05:22.622 --> 05:24.222
And they say you're not
supposed to live there,

05:24.224 --> 05:27.058
but those people
never check, so...

05:27.060 --> 05:29.160
She's 11.
Well, you know
I'm not good at this!

05:29.162 --> 05:32.363
All right. You see
that little gift shop?

05:32.365 --> 05:33.465
The shopkeeper
is in the middle

05:33.467 --> 05:35.500
of picking something
real nice out for her.

05:35.502 --> 05:38.069
You go, get it. Take the credit.
It's fine.

05:39.306 --> 05:40.839
Where you staying?

05:40.841 --> 05:43.175
Well, the easiest thing
would be just to --

05:43.177 --> 05:45.911
-No. Don't. No wrestling.
-Please.

05:45.913 --> 05:48.213
I love you!

05:51.185 --> 05:53.785
Stan: "Kumbhakarna."

05:53.787 --> 05:58.724
♪♪

05:58.726 --> 06:01.126
"Kum...bha..."

06:01.128 --> 06:03.329
[Doorbell rings]

06:03.331 --> 06:04.796
[Pen drops]

06:06.067 --> 06:07.565
Dude!

06:07.567 --> 06:08.867
I'm not home.

06:11.304 --> 06:12.805
[Door closes]

06:12.807 --> 06:15.207
[Laughs] You got me.

06:15.209 --> 06:18.544
Oh, man. [Laughs]

06:18.546 --> 06:20.279
Hey. L-L-Listen there --
there, Kenny.

06:20.281 --> 06:22.013
A-After that whole thing
in the bar --

06:22.015 --> 06:25.083
Wait, wait. Before
you say anything else...

06:25.085 --> 06:26.618
I've come to make amends.

06:26.620 --> 06:28.487
-You got sober?
-No.

06:28.489 --> 06:32.090
But there's a new thing
called Drunk Sobriety.

06:32.092 --> 06:35.761
It's -- It's like being sober,
but you can still drink.

06:35.763 --> 06:37.295
I'm listening.

06:37.297 --> 06:40.098
♪♪

06:40.100 --> 06:43.168
-Ah!
-That ain't all bad.

06:43.170 --> 06:45.570
[Slurring] Oh!
I got you something.

06:45.572 --> 06:47.305
I almost forgot.

06:47.307 --> 06:49.741
Huh.

06:49.743 --> 06:52.644
Come he-r-r-r-re.

06:52.646 --> 06:54.712
This is for you.

06:54.714 --> 06:57.116
What in the hell
is<i> that?</i>

06:57.118 --> 06:59.184
I made this for you.

06:59.186 --> 07:01.720
I'm not gonna lie.

07:01.722 --> 07:04.323
With these hands.

07:04.325 --> 07:07.726
[Whispering] I have
a porcelain tree.

07:07.728 --> 07:10.129
[Whispering]
What the hell is it?

07:12.399 --> 07:15.266
-What is this?
-I don't want it.

07:15.268 --> 07:17.136
-Really?
-Eh.

07:17.138 --> 07:19.204
C-Can I have it?

07:19.206 --> 07:21.006
Yeah, think, uh --

07:21.008 --> 07:24.309
Think of it as...
my gift to you.

07:27.347 --> 07:29.648
[Claps hands]

07:31.685 --> 07:33.952
[Voice breaking] Ohh.

07:33.954 --> 07:36.955
Stan.

07:36.957 --> 07:39.758
I know. I know.

07:39.760 --> 07:42.427
Well, like I said...

07:42.429 --> 07:44.029
[Clears throat]

07:44.031 --> 07:46.832
I just -- I just dropped by
to say hello.

07:46.834 --> 07:48.233
Oh.

07:48.235 --> 07:50.969
I-I don't -- I don't want
to impose or anything.

07:50.971 --> 07:53.205
No, you c--

07:54.641 --> 07:56.575
Oh, for the love of God.

07:57.778 --> 07:59.711
Oh, n--

07:59.713 --> 08:03.648
[Sleepily] Don't shave
my head and paint me.

08:03.650 --> 08:06.919
Don't -- Don't shave
my head and paint me.

08:06.921 --> 08:08.219
<i> [Creatures growling on TV]</i>

08:08.221 --> 08:10.455
Japanese official:<i> Soon</i>
<i> they will destroy Tokyo!</i>

08:10.457 --> 08:12.591
Cheryl:
<i> Like you destroyed us?</i>

08:12.593 --> 08:14.259
<i> Really, Cheryl? Now?</i>

08:14.261 --> 08:18.096
<i> [Creature growling,</i>
<i> people screaming]</i>

08:18.098 --> 08:20.999
Dad, why is there
a man in my bed?

08:21.001 --> 08:25.403
Oh, yeah, that's, uh --
that's Evie's ex-husband.

08:25.405 --> 08:28.806
Why is he covered
in cobwebs?

08:28.808 --> 08:30.275
I beg your pardon?

08:33.680 --> 08:35.914
What in the hell?

08:35.916 --> 08:41.420
♪♪

08:44.957 --> 08:46.424
♪♪

08:46.426 --> 08:48.259
[Doorbell rings]

08:48.261 --> 08:50.428
Like Grand Central Station
in this dump.

08:50.430 --> 08:51.629
[Whimpers]

08:51.631 --> 08:54.032
[Eerie music playing]

08:54.034 --> 08:56.635
-Where is Stan?
-Where is Stan?

08:56.637 --> 08:58.069
What?

08:58.071 --> 09:01.172
-Where is Stan?
-Where is Stan?

09:01.174 --> 09:02.807
[Softly] I'm Stan!

09:03.544 --> 09:06.344
-Then who has the relic?
-Then who has the relic?

09:07.581 --> 09:09.714
-Whee!
-Whee!

09:09.716 --> 09:15.854
♪♪

09:15.856 --> 09:18.189
Kenny: Anybody know
what's going on here?

09:18.191 --> 09:20.125
-The relic was for you.
-The relic was for you.

09:20.127 --> 09:23.862
Yeah, well, I didn't want it.
What's with all the cobwebs?

09:23.864 --> 09:25.129
-They're not cobs.
-They're not cobs.

09:25.131 --> 09:27.266
-Catty-pilly silkies.
-Catty-pilly silkies.

09:27.268 --> 09:29.934
-He's transforming.
-He's transforming.

09:29.936 --> 09:31.802
[Ominous music plays]

09:31.804 --> 09:36.941
♪♪

09:36.943 --> 09:39.477
Anyway, your ex-husband's
here uninvited again,

09:39.479 --> 09:41.547
and he's turning
into a caterpillar.

09:41.549 --> 09:43.414
No, that's it.
<i> Hasta luego.</i>

09:43.416 --> 09:45.216
[Receiver hangs up]

09:45.218 --> 09:48.886
♪♪

09:48.888 --> 09:52.023
I'm going out. When I return, I
assume I will have my room back.

09:52.025 --> 09:55.093
-Where ya goin'?
-I am taking these downtown

09:55.095 --> 09:57.228
to the miniature
Willard's Mill display.

09:57.230 --> 09:58.963
-Who's doing that?
-Chamber of Commerce.

09:58.965 --> 10:00.765
They want the town
to be known for something

10:00.767 --> 10:02.768
other than, you know,
people being burned alive.

10:02.770 --> 10:04.903
Oh, I see,
so being burned alive's

10:04.905 --> 10:06.838
not good enough
for 'em, huh?

10:06.840 --> 10:09.841
Everybody liked it fine
back in<i> my</i> day!

10:09.843 --> 10:13.144
Twins: Ken says you may leave,
but leave now.

10:13.146 --> 10:15.714
-[Sternly] You stay.
-Eww.

10:15.716 --> 10:18.750
Kenny: Bibi! Fifi!
I need you!

10:20.520 --> 10:22.154
-Whee!
-Whee!

10:22.156 --> 10:24.822
I got here
as fast as I could.

10:26.159 --> 10:30.128
Kenny: Evie, is that you?!
Come in here!

10:30.130 --> 10:32.463
[Evie groans]

10:34.001 --> 10:35.667
Hahh...

10:35.669 --> 10:38.669
♪♪

10:38.671 --> 10:40.671
Evie:
What did you do?!

10:40.673 --> 10:43.007
Why do you always assume
it's something<i> I</i> did?

10:43.009 --> 10:44.676
-You're upsetting him!
-You're upsetting him!

10:44.678 --> 10:47.679
Easy, girls.
It's okay. It's okay.

10:47.681 --> 10:50.481
[Chuckles]
You must love this.

10:50.483 --> 10:52.617
They are adorable,
aren't they?

10:52.619 --> 10:54.353
They'll do anything I say.
Watch this.

10:54.355 --> 10:56.021
And...wrestle!

10:57.357 --> 10:58.389
No, no, no.
No, no, no, it's okay.

10:58.391 --> 11:00.292
We don't need
to see them wrestle.

11:00.294 --> 11:02.027
I'm a big
wrestling guy.

11:02.029 --> 11:04.328
♪♪

11:04.330 --> 11:05.764
Twins:
He who possesses the relic

11:05.766 --> 11:08.132
will transform
into a caterpillar.

11:08.134 --> 11:12.370
But it was not for Ken.
It was for Stan.

11:12.372 --> 11:13.938
Evie: That's right!

11:13.940 --> 11:16.107
The shopkeeper wanted
<i> you</i> to have it.
Oh.

11:16.109 --> 11:19.310
And then Stan would transform
and ingest you!

11:19.312 --> 11:21.846
-Ew.
-Twins: Pfft!

11:21.848 --> 11:25.183
Okay, so the shopkeeper
is a demon sent by Eccles?

11:25.185 --> 11:26.485
[Twins chuckling]

11:26.487 --> 11:27.652
Oh.
What happens next?

11:27.654 --> 11:29.854
Well, I'll tell you
what happens next.

11:29.856 --> 11:32.457
I eat Stan, and then
you and I merge as one.

11:32.459 --> 11:36.661
Evie, together we are
gonna make a gorgeous moth.

11:36.663 --> 11:38.029
No, Kenny.

11:38.031 --> 11:42.000
Together we are<i> not</i> going
to make a gorgeous moth.

11:42.002 --> 11:45.803
Evie, you are gonna
love it in my cocoon.

11:45.805 --> 11:48.340
Well, Kenny, I'm not
getting in your cocoon.

11:48.342 --> 11:50.742
[Chuckles] You're
already in my cocoon.

11:50.744 --> 11:53.945
This whole house
is my cocoon!

11:53.947 --> 11:56.948
-[Laughs evilly]
-[Twins giggling]

11:56.950 --> 11:59.284
[Laughing evilly,
screeching]

11:59.286 --> 12:02.487
[Twins squeaking]

12:02.489 --> 12:04.756
Oh-ho-ho! Cocoon!

12:04.758 --> 12:06.892
Stan, the windows.

12:06.894 --> 12:09.360
This whole house
is my cocoon!

12:09.362 --> 12:12.430
Oh, run if you want!
You're in my cocoon!

12:12.432 --> 12:13.865
-You can never escape!
-You can never escape!

12:13.867 --> 12:15.433
Yeah, sure thing, gals.

12:15.435 --> 12:16.901
-Whee!
-Whee!

12:16.903 --> 12:19.838
Evie, let's go.

12:19.840 --> 12:20.972
We should change that to

12:20.974 --> 12:23.374
"You can escape,
but only if you want to!"

12:23.376 --> 12:26.044
Well, I guess
we should tell him.

12:26.046 --> 12:28.179
[Door closes]

12:28.181 --> 12:29.580
Or not.

12:29.582 --> 12:33.785
-I don't really feel like it.
-Yeah, I'm not into it.

12:35.588 --> 12:36.754
[Bell jingles]

12:36.756 --> 12:38.557
Here we go.

12:40.460 --> 12:42.927
[Door closes, bell jingles]

12:42.929 --> 12:44.896
-Where is he?
-Where is who?

12:44.898 --> 12:46.464
The other shopkeeper.

12:46.466 --> 12:47.899
There is no other
shopkeeper.

12:47.901 --> 12:51.402
Yeah, the guy in the silk robe
with the long, white beard.

12:51.404 --> 12:54.739
Oh, that's our sister store,
Tired Asian Stereotypes.

12:54.741 --> 12:57.341
It's just down the block.
Wow! What?!

12:57.343 --> 12:59.544
What did he try to do,
sell you a gremlin?

12:59.546 --> 13:02.147
-Okay. I beg your pardon?
-Well, Evie, he's got a point.

13:02.149 --> 13:05.683
You -- Same old Japanese guy
from those Kung Fu movies, huh?

13:05.685 --> 13:07.585
-Kung fu is Chinese.
-Eh, same thing.

13:07.587 --> 13:08.954
-It really isn't.
-No, it's not.

13:08.956 --> 13:10.521
Ah, d-- I know that!

13:10.523 --> 13:12.958
Just tryin' to make him
lose his cool

13:12.960 --> 13:15.494
so that he'll reveal
whether or not he's a demon.

13:15.496 --> 13:16.494
Ohh!

13:16.496 --> 13:18.696
-I'm not a demon.
-Oh, yeah, huh?

13:18.698 --> 13:20.831
Only one way to figure out
whether you're a demon or not,

13:20.833 --> 13:23.168
'cause a demon would
never let me do<i> this.</i>

13:23.971 --> 13:26.404
Well, he ain't a demon.
That's for damn sure.

13:26.406 --> 13:30.241
Would you like to press charges
against Mr. Miller?

13:30.243 --> 13:31.876
Yes, I would.

13:31.878 --> 13:33.178
Evie: Eh. Okay.

13:33.180 --> 13:36.447
So he's not a demon, but we know
now that there was one.

13:36.449 --> 13:38.516
If the answer's not in there,
it's gotta be

13:38.518 --> 13:40.318
in Claire's library, right?
Let's go.

13:40.320 --> 13:41.953
Hold on!
I need to file a report.

13:41.955 --> 13:44.922
Ah, no, no, Leon, you don't
need to file a report.

13:44.924 --> 13:47.658
This gentleman has done
absolutely nothing wrong.

13:47.660 --> 13:50.996
I know that! He's filing
a report against<i> you!</i>

13:50.998 --> 13:52.597
Well, if he's willing
to apologize,

13:52.599 --> 13:54.065
I'll forget
the whole thing.

13:54.067 --> 13:56.100
-Why should I apologize?
-Fair enough.

13:56.102 --> 14:00.138
I'll be the bigger man
and just walk away.

14:01.408 --> 14:04.675
So, what happened
to the erotic bakery?

14:04.677 --> 14:08.212
[<i> "My Thoughts Get Caught</i>
<i> In My Mouth"</i> plays ]

14:08.214 --> 14:12.616
♪♪

14:12.618 --> 14:14.686
♪ There's a radio inside of me ♪

14:14.688 --> 14:18.923
♪ It wants to play a song
if I can think of one ♪

14:18.925 --> 14:21.091
♪♪

14:21.093 --> 14:23.160
♪ I find I have so much to say ♪

14:23.162 --> 14:25.297
♪ And music starts to play ♪

14:25.299 --> 14:28.366
♪ But words there come none ♪

14:28.368 --> 14:33.437
♪ Because my thoughts
get caught in my mouth ♪

14:33.439 --> 14:37.108
♪ My thoughts get
caught in my mouth ♪

14:37.110 --> 14:39.110
♪ I can swallow them back down ♪

14:39.112 --> 14:43.114
♪ But they'll only turn around
when I'm thinking of you ♪

14:43.116 --> 14:45.650
♪ 'Cause when
I'm thinking of you ♪

14:45.652 --> 14:49.387
♪ My thoughts get caught ♪

14:49.389 --> 14:51.856
♪ In my m-o-o-outh ♪

14:51.858 --> 14:53.991
[Screeching ]
♪ In my m-o-o-outh ♪

14:53.993 --> 14:55.927
[Creatures screeching]

14:55.929 --> 15:00.431
[All screaming]

15:03.937 --> 15:06.404
[Engine shuts off]

15:06.406 --> 15:08.272
Ohh...

15:08.274 --> 15:13.411
♪♪

15:13.413 --> 15:16.681
Okay. I'm gonna go straight
for Claire's library.

15:16.683 --> 15:19.217
You just buy me
as much time as you can.

15:19.219 --> 15:20.818
Got it.

15:20.820 --> 15:24.288
♪♪

15:24.290 --> 15:26.424
Ugh.

15:26.426 --> 15:31.763
♪♪

15:31.765 --> 15:37.101
♪♪

15:37.103 --> 15:38.636
Fifi: So I said, "You have
got to get insurance."

15:38.638 --> 15:39.704
Bibi:
Oh, I know. Okay.

15:39.706 --> 15:41.839
Four kids, a cat,
and a skateboard?

15:41.841 --> 15:43.507
-Hello?
-He's too old for skateboarding.

15:43.509 --> 15:45.109
[Laughs]
Try telling him that.

15:45.111 --> 15:48.913
Twins: Hiii...

15:48.915 --> 15:50.581
Mary-Kate, Ashley.

15:50.583 --> 15:52.116
Twins:
Ken is no longer here.

15:52.118 --> 15:56.387
Evie: Stan! He's not here.
I just talked to Leon.

15:56.389 --> 15:58.055
We gotta
get back downtown.

15:58.057 --> 15:59.590
Hi, guys...

15:59.592 --> 16:02.660
Ken has achieved perfection
and left the cocoon.

16:02.662 --> 16:05.797
Is there a way to
break the curse, uh,

16:05.799 --> 16:08.199
without hurting Ken?

16:08.201 --> 16:10.535
All his power
is held in the relic.

16:10.537 --> 16:13.137
Destroy the relic,
and you end the curse.

16:13.139 --> 16:16.874
Ohh! Fantastic!
Where's the relic?

16:16.876 --> 16:19.144
He ate it.

16:19.146 --> 16:23.214
Nothing was ever easy
with him.

16:23.216 --> 16:25.616
[People screaming,
siren wailing]

16:25.618 --> 16:28.119
-Woman: Run!
-Man: Here! Take my hand!

16:28.121 --> 16:29.821
Man: Keep moving!

16:29.823 --> 16:32.056
This way! This way!

16:32.058 --> 16:35.293
[People screaming,
siren wailing]

16:35.295 --> 16:40.965
♪♪

16:40.967 --> 16:46.571
♪♪

16:46.573 --> 16:48.873
Oh, good God!

16:48.875 --> 16:50.808
Miniature
Willard's Mill!

16:50.810 --> 16:51.977
Ken, no!

16:51.979 --> 16:56.047
[People screaming]

16:56.049 --> 16:58.449
We've got to figure out
how to get that relic out!

16:58.451 --> 17:00.985
Ah, you could hold him down, and
I could cut open his stomach.

17:00.987 --> 17:02.787
That's your solution
to everything.
Yeah.

17:02.789 --> 17:05.923
No, we need -- What's that stuff
that makes you throw up?

17:05.925 --> 17:08.259
-That guy on Bravo?
-No! The liquid!

17:08.261 --> 17:10.595
[Snaps fingers]
Ipecac! We need a lot of that.

17:10.597 --> 17:13.765
Oh, I have two Super Soakers
full of spoilt milk in my car.

17:15.135 --> 17:17.735
-I'll go get 'em.
-Make it quick!

17:17.737 --> 17:19.270
It won't be long before

17:19.272 --> 17:21.939
all of miniature
Willard's Mill is destroyed!

17:21.941 --> 17:27.812
[Screeching]

17:32.084 --> 17:33.251
[All screaming]

17:33.253 --> 17:35.253
Look sharp!

17:37.056 --> 17:40.358
Okay, try to get as much liquid
in his mouth as you can.

17:40.360 --> 17:42.159
[Screeching]

17:42.161 --> 17:44.195
Ready...

17:44.197 --> 17:47.064
aim...

17:47.066 --> 17:48.566
fire!

17:48.568 --> 17:50.768
♪♪

17:50.770 --> 17:53.037
[Growling]

17:53.039 --> 17:55.072
Lenny! No!

17:55.074 --> 17:58.410
[Growling]

18:00.113 --> 18:01.979
[Screeching]

18:01.981 --> 18:08.420
♪♪

18:08.422 --> 18:12.790
Evie: Ugh. I've seen Kenny
when he's like this.

18:12.792 --> 18:14.792
Well, not like<i> this.</i>

18:14.794 --> 18:17.261
Panicked male:
We got to evacuate the city!

18:17.263 --> 18:19.531
Whose shoes are these?!

18:19.533 --> 18:22.400
[Growling and screeching]

18:22.402 --> 18:24.869
♪♪

18:24.871 --> 18:26.737
Stan: Oof!

18:26.739 --> 18:28.606
[Car horn honking]

18:28.608 --> 18:33.945
♪♪

18:33.947 --> 18:36.213
Panicked female:
I can't find my harmonica!

18:36.215 --> 18:39.217
Damn it!
I can't get a clear shot!

18:40.920 --> 18:43.288
Young shopkeeper:
Nature finds a balance.

18:43.290 --> 18:45.623
Let them fight.

18:45.625 --> 18:48.693
[Glass shatters]

18:48.695 --> 18:52.830
♪♪

18:52.832 --> 18:53.898
Ohh!

18:53.900 --> 18:56.768
Panicked male:
This is like a nightmare.

18:56.770 --> 18:57.836
-Honey, let's go.
-Is it dead?!

18:57.838 --> 18:59.703
Let's just go to the park!

18:59.705 --> 19:02.307
Leon: The kids worked
so hard on that!

19:02.309 --> 19:04.742
♪♪

19:04.744 --> 19:06.177
Ohh.

19:06.179 --> 19:12.050
♪♪

19:12.052 --> 19:13.852
[Snarling]

19:14.588 --> 19:17.589
Evie: Why is he afraid
of the cross?

19:17.591 --> 19:20.391
♪♪

19:20.393 --> 19:23.794
Wait!
Now<i> he's</i> afraid of the cross?

19:23.796 --> 19:27.999
♪♪

19:28.001 --> 19:30.468
Panicked male:
What's going on?

19:30.470 --> 19:32.203
I want chicken!

19:32.205 --> 19:40.344
♪♪

19:40.346 --> 19:41.612
Ohh.

19:41.614 --> 19:44.815
♪♪

19:44.817 --> 19:47.886
[Growling]

19:47.888 --> 19:49.453
[Squish]

19:49.455 --> 19:52.356
Aaah!

19:52.358 --> 19:55.360
[Growls]

19:55.362 --> 19:56.594
No!

19:56.596 --> 20:03.034
♪♪

20:03.637 --> 20:05.236
Aah!

20:08.241 --> 20:10.975
What...am I doing?

20:10.977 --> 20:13.144
[Whimpering]

20:14.380 --> 20:19.650
This isn't what I wanted
my life to be about.

20:19.652 --> 20:22.119
I'm comin' home, Margaret.

20:22.121 --> 20:23.988
-[Growls]
-Aah.

20:23.990 --> 20:25.055
Yes!

20:25.057 --> 20:27.525
[Stomach growling]

20:27.527 --> 20:31.062
[Wheezing]

20:31.064 --> 20:35.866
Kenny: Aaaaah!

20:35.868 --> 20:37.402
♪♪

20:41.341 --> 20:43.274
-Yeah! Yes!
-Yes!

20:43.276 --> 20:45.009
[Laughs]

20:45.011 --> 20:46.844
Yes!

20:48.214 --> 20:50.014
[Kenny groaning]

20:50.016 --> 20:52.950
-Kenny.
-Ugh. Yeah?

20:52.952 --> 20:56.220
Ugh.
No hard feelings?

20:56.222 --> 20:57.822
Of course not.

20:57.824 --> 21:00.157
Pretty good battle.

21:00.159 --> 21:02.827
Good fighter.

21:02.829 --> 21:05.296
-Ohh!
-What day is it?

21:05.298 --> 21:06.831
Saturday.

21:06.833 --> 21:09.233
I didn't miss Grace's
birthday party!

21:09.235 --> 21:11.502
No. It's tomorrow.

21:11.504 --> 21:13.904
Hey! You wouldn't want
to keep that suit

21:13.906 --> 21:16.173
one more day, would ya?

21:16.175 --> 21:17.709
Yeah, it seems
we got a, uh,

21:17.711 --> 21:19.444
little girl with
a birthday party!

21:19.446 --> 21:22.247
Lenny: Birthday party?
I'll do it!

21:22.249 --> 21:24.649
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

21:24.651 --> 21:25.916
♪ La la la ♪

21:25.918 --> 21:27.452
♪ La la la la la la ♪

21:27.454 --> 21:28.719
♪ La la la ♪

21:28.721 --> 21:30.187
♪ La la la la la la ♪

21:30.189 --> 21:31.855
Lenny:
Who are we waving at?

21:31.857 --> 21:34.124
-♪ La la la la la la ♪
-♪ La la la ♪

21:34.126 --> 21:36.193
♪ La la la la la la ♪

21:36.195 --> 21:39.196
♪ La-la-la ♪

21:39.198 --> 21:43.167
Panicked female:
I can't find my harmonica!
